# Analysis Assessment
Reading the article and carefully going through the analysis and results helps to understand the findings better.

The article seemed complex at first (a lot of consider), but in the end everything was reduced to ANOVAs and different combination of variables.

‚úÖ Plots made it easier to understand the results.

‚ùì Why is there no consistency among them (some report YES responses, others YES and NO)?
---
# Analysis Assessment
Some considerations...
- The article failed to report that they were going to run an extra ANOVA for the psychological questionnaires AND did not mention them in their discussion. It could have been assessed better and used as a relevant factor.
---
# Analysis Assessment
Some considerations on EEG...
- Many details are not reported in the methodology or not included at all in the article. Some of those, like the time window of interest or what component does the study focus in are commonly included and carefully analyzed.

- My guess is that the researchers either failed to report those details. The data included can not be obtain without thinking about the analysis prior of collecting data.
---
# Analysis Assessment
Some considerations...
- The article does not report how was any of the statistic information obtained. Did the researches use R? Any special package? Did they do it with any other programming tool or without one at all?

- The article does not share code nor data. This study would not be replicable nor meets the standards to be consider reliable (probably a strong statement, but probably true).
